Radiological examination of cerebral circulation in cerebrovascular disorders. The authors provide the results of radiological examinations of cerebral circulation in 215 patients aged 16 to 67 years with different periods of cervical osteochondrosis. The intensity of hemispheric hemocirculation derangement depends on the stage of osteochondrosis. At the same time cerebral circulation disorders running their course by the type of transitory disturbances are not specific for the given group of patients and can also be seen in patients suffering from other diseases of the brain.